# Equity Financing Term Sheet

Non-binding term sheet that captures economic, governance, and investor rights terms for a preferred stock financing.

## Prerequisites

1. **Company details**: legal name, jurisdiction of incorporation, current cap table (fully diluted), existing charter/bylaws, option plan size
2. **Round details**: series designation, lead investor, total raise, pre-money valuation (or price per share)
3. **Governance baseline**: current board composition, existing investor rights, major contracts or debt covenants
4. **Deal constraints**: closing timeline, regulatory or industry constraints, expense cap expectations

## Output Structure / Process

### Document Header

| Field | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Company | [Company Legal Name], a [State] corporation |
| Series | [Series A Preferred Stock] |
| Date | [Month Day, Year] |
| Lead Investor | [Lead Investor Legal Name] |

### Non-Binding / Binding Split

| Provision | Status |
| --- | --- |
| Economic terms | Non-binding |
| Governance terms | Non-binding |
| Investor rights | Non-binding |
| Confidentiality | Binding |
| Exclusivity / No-shop | Binding |
| Expenses | Binding |
| Governing law / venue | Binding |

### Economic Terms

| Term | Drafting Instructions / Placeholders |
| --- | --- |
| Amount Raised | $[TBD] (or range $[Min]–$[Max]) |
| Pre-Money Valuation | $[TBD] |
| Price Per Share | $[Pre-money] ÷ [Fully Diluted Capitalization Pre-Financing] = $[TBD] |
| Security | [Series A Convertible Preferred Stock] |
| Use of Proceeds | [General corporate purposes / R&D / sales expansion] |

**Fully Diluted Capitalization Definition (include in term sheet):** common stock outstanding + options (granted and reserved) + warrants + convertible securities + other equity-linked instruments.

### Dividends

| Term | Options |
| --- | --- |
| Dividend Rate | [Non-cumulative] or [Cumulative at X% of Original Purchase Price] |
| Priority | Senior to common and junior preferred, if any |
| Payment | When, as, and if declared by Board |

### Liquidation Preference

| Term | Options |
| --- | --- |
| Preference Amount | [1x] original purchase price |
| Participation | [Non-participating] or [Participating] |
| Participation Cap | [None] or [Xx total return cap] |
| Waterfall | Preferred first; then as-converted to common |

### Conversion

| Term | Standard |
| --- | --- |
| Optional Conversion | 1:1 into common at holder’s option |
| Automatic Conversion | Upon Qualified IPO (define $ proceeds and $/share) |
| Adjustments | Stock splits, dividends, recapitalizations |

### Anti-Dilution

| Term | Standard |
| --- | --- |
| Type | [Broad-based weighted average] (default) |
| Excluded Issuances | Option plan grants within reserve; acquisitions; equipment leases; strategic partnerships; debt financing |

**Weighted Average Formula (include if used):**
```
CP2 = CP1 * (A + B) / (A + C)
CP1 = prior conversion price
CP2 = new conversion price
A = fully diluted shares pre-issuance
B = total consideration received ÷ CP1
C = new shares issued in dilutive issuance
```

